Paramedics found both vehicles off the side of the road with several children on the pavement. JOHANNESBURG An investigation is underway to determine the cause of a taxi crash that left 16 children injured in Centurion.It s understood that a taxi and car collided on Hammerfest Road on Monday.Paramedics found both vehicles on the side of the road with several children on the pavement.Spokesperson ER24 s Russel Meiring says: They assessed the patients and found that 16 people had sustained minor to moderate injuries, 14 of those were treated and transported to hospitals for further medical care. (Edited by Leeto M Khoza)